-- int_deduped_billing.sql
```sql
-- Deduplicate billing events to one row per subscription per month
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        subscription_id,
        event_month,
        amount,
        ROW_NUMBER() OVER (
            PARTITION BY subscription_id, event_month
            ORDER BY event_id DESC
        ) AS row_num
    FROM {{ ref('stg_billing_events') }}
)

SELECT
    subscription_id,
    event_month,
    amount
FROM source
WHERE row_num = 1
```

-- int_subscriptions_enriched.sql
```sql
-- Enrich subscriptions with user, company, and plan attributes
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        s.subscription_id,
        s.user_id,
        s.plan_id,
        s.started_at,
        s.ended_at,
        s.status,
        COALESCE(p.tier, '(unknown)') AS tier,
        COALESCE(c.industry, '(unknown)') AS industry
    FROM {{ ref('stg_subscriptions') }} s
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('stg_users') }} u
        ON u.user_id = s.user_id
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('stg_companies') }} c
        ON c.company_id = u.company_id
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('stg_plans') }} p
        ON p.plan_id = s.plan_id
)

SELECT
    subscription_id,
    user_id,
    plan_id,
    started_at,
    ended_at,
    status,
    tier,
    industry
FROM source
```

-- fct_monthly_subscription_metrics.sql
```sql
-- Monthly subscription metrics aggregated by tier and industry
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        b.event_month AS month,
        e.tier,
        e.industry,
        e.subscription_id,
        e.user_id,
        b.amount
    FROM {{ ref('int_deduped_billing') }} b
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('int_subscriptions_enriched') }} e
        ON e.subscription_id = b.subscription_id
)

SELECT
    month,
    tier,
    industry,
    COUNT(DISTINCT subscription_id) AS active_subscriptions,
    SUM(amount) AS total_mrr,
    COUNT(DISTINCT user_id) AS unique_users
FROM source
GROUP BY
    month,
    tier,
    industry
ORDER BY
    month ASC,
    tier ASC,
    industry ASC
